k, such as social engineering and human violence, agency and consciousness, Freudianism and the creative process, evolution and the philosophy of the future, virtual reality and epistemological illusion, and science fiction and socio-cultural policy. This unique collection also includes "Smart Robots," a previously unpublished essay by Lem. Contributors include Peter Butko (Southern Mississippi), Istvan Csicsery-Ronay Jr (DePauw), Katherine Hayles (California at Los Angeles), Jerzy Jarzebski (Jagiellonian, University Cracow), Michael Kandel (Modern Language Association), Stanislaw Lem, Paisley Livingston (Lingnan University, Hong Kong), Krzysztof Loska (Jagiellonian University), and Peter Swirski (Hong Kong).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Eastern (see also Russian & Former Soviet Union).2bisacsh1 aButko, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCsicsery-Ronay, Istvan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHayles, N. Katherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarzeębski, Jerzy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKandel, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLem, Stanislaw, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLivingston, Paisley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoska, Krzysztof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwirski, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9